>...
>> These licenses are available for the practice of standards that NIST
>> *may* develop. DSA is one. A key management standard is another. I
>> don't know where anyone got the idea that Clipper or Capstone are
>> "mandated" by this deal.
>
>Read appendix A. It states that a condition of licence for a semi manafacurer
>id to support the key eschrow deal. If you don't support key eschrow, no
